Q1. Smallest unit Kubernetes deploys?

 B. Pod

Q2. Object used to expose pods to network traffic?

 C. Service

Q3. Service type for internal communication only?

 C. ClusterIP

Q4. Access app using <NodeIP>:<Port> — Which Service?

 B. NodePort

Q5. Cloud environments use which Service to expose apps externally?

 C. LoadBalancer

Q6. Pod deleted accidentally — which can recreate it?

 C. Pod managed by Deployment

Q7. Pod type used for initialization tasks?

 B. Init Pod

Q8. Containers inside same pod communicate using?

 C. Same IP address

Q9. Service that assigns stable internal IP?

 C. ClusterIP

Q10. Service created but traffic not reaching Pod — most common reason?

 B. Label mismatch

Q11. Component providing DNS-based service discovery?

 C. CoreDNS

Q12. Pod that always runs on a specific node?

 C. Static Pod

Q13. Service exposing fixed port on every node?

 B. NodePort

Q14. Pods want to access app using DNS name — which Service?

 C. ClusterIP

Q15. Command to show Pod IP?

 C. kubectl get pods -o wide

Q16. LoadBalancer service in local cluster — what happens?

 B. External IP stays pending

Q17. Pod used to support main app (logging/monitoring)?

 C. Sidecar Pod

Q18. Which Service field decides which pods get traffic?

 C. selector

Q19. Command to list all services?

 B. kubectl get svc

Q20. Two pods communicate — recommended way?

 B. Use Service name